values.title: Tramway
values.desc: It is mandatory to stop completely at the stop line, or if not available, as close to the crossing road or railway track as possible, before continuing. Vehicles must also give way to other traffic, or trains.

values.title: Distance to pedestrian crossing
values.desc: Priority at all following crossroads up to an end of priority road, give way or stop sign.

values.title: Children
values.desc: Warns about dangerous crossroads where the road this sign is placed on has priority. Crossing roads have give way or stop signs.

values.title: Cyclist
values.desc: Restriction is for motor vehicles with more than two wheels and an allowed total weight limit above the given weight limit.

values.title: Moose
values.desc: Restriction is for a vehicle including all of its goods.

values.title: Reindeer
values.desc: Restriction is for a vehicle including all of its goods.

values.title: Deer
values.desc: Restriction is for a vehicle including all of its goods.

values.title: Cattle
values.desc: Restriction is for each vehicle in the case of a lorry.

values.title: Sheep
values.desc: Restriction is for the combined weight in the case of a lorry, though no single vehicle is permitted above the limit either.

values.title: Two-way traffic
values.desc: No vehicle with weight above the given limit for each axle, and maximum 150% of the limit for each bogie.

values.title: Traffic queues likely
values.desc: Vehicle is not permitted to continue until the action described is done.

values.title: Low-flying aircraft
values.desc: Vehicle is not permitted to continue until the action described is done.

values.title: Military activity
values.desc: Vehicle is not permitted to continue until the action described is done.

values.title: Crosswinds
values.desc: For the next intersection unless otherwise stated with a supplementary sign.

values.title: Traffic accident
values.desc: For the next intersection unless otherwise stated with a supplementary sign.

values.title: Skiers
values.desc: Until and including the next crossroads.

values.title: Riders
values.desc: Restriction is for overtaking motor vehicles with more than two wheels. Overtaking on the right side is permitted by normal traffic rules.

values.title: Other danger
values.desc: Restriction is for lorries with a total weight above 3.500 kg overtaking motor vehicles with more than two wheels. Overtaking on the right side is permitted by normal traffic rules.

values.title: (1) Polar bear
values.desc: Speed limit of given km/h until new speed limit, end of special speed limit, speed limit zone or any pedestrian precinct sign

values.title: (2) Snowmobiles
values.desc: This means a general speed limit of 50 km/h in populated areas and 80 km/h in rural areas by law.

values.title: Yield (Give way)
values.desc: Speed limit of given km/h until end of speed limit, end of speed limit zone or any pedestrian precinct sign

values.title: Stop
values.desc: No stops until the next crossing road or until another sign ends it.

values.title: Priority road
values.desc: No parking on the side of the road where the sign is until the next crossing road or until another sign ends it.

values.title: End of priority road
values.desc: Parking permitted until end of parking zone sign. Often with supplementary text about when the sign is valid.

values.title: Priority crossroads
values.desc: No parking permitted until end of parking zone sign. Often with supplementary text about when the sign is valid.

values.title: Give way for oncoming traffic
values.desc: Speed limit is 80 km/h unless another limit is set, which it normally is. 110 km/h is the highest limit found, and is set on the highest standard motorways. Lower limits may be set on lower standard or busier roads.

values.title: Priority over oncoming traffic
values.desc: Speed limit is 80 km/h unless another limit is specifically set. Some are signposted to 90 km/h.

values.title: No entry
values.desc: Only vehicles with allowed total weight higher than indicated can use this lane.

values.title: Road closed to all traffic
values.desc: Only vehicles with more than indicated occupants including driver can use this lane. Buses and taxis, regardless of how many occupants can also use this lane.[b]

values.title: No motor vehicles
values.desc: ("Møteplass" in Norwegian.) Used frequently on long stretches of single-track roads. Parking forbidden.

values.title: No tractors or motor vehicles slower than 40 km/h
values.desc: Road physically closed

values.title: No motor cycles or mopeds
values.desc: Side-road physically closed

values.title: No lorries
values.desc: Road closed for vehicles

values.title: No cyclists
values.desc: Side-road closed for vehicles

values.title: No pedestrians
values.desc: Merging by the “zipper method”.

values.title: No pedestrians or cyclists
values.desc: Oncoming lane has to adapt. Merging by the “zipper method”.

values.title: No riders
values.desc: This lane has to adapt. Merging by the “zipper method”.

values.title: No transport of dangerous goods
values.desc: The ending lane has to give way.

values.title: Total weight limit
values.desc: Denotes the number of lanes and what direction they go.

values.title: Width limit
values.desc: May be used in conjunction with road works.

values.title: Height limit
values.desc: The speed limit is "walking speed."

values.title: Length limit
values.desc: Motor vehicles are normally prohibited in pedestrian zone. If exemption is granted by a supplementary sign, the speed limit is "walking speed."

values.title: Weight limit for vehicles
values.desc: To be used only in case of vehicle breakdown or other emergency.

values.title: Weight limit for lorries
values.desc: A flashing yellow indicator is also placed at the end of speed measurement zone. This will flash if the vehicle's measured average speed exceeded the speed limit.

values.title: Axle weight limit

Must have a yellow background if it's a temporary sign, or an orange background if it provides information about detours.

values.title: End of special speed limit

values.desc: Signifies a route that leads to the given route.

values.title: No parking

values.desc: Symbol may be used on service signs.

values.title: End of parking zone
values.desc: Generally only used under special circumstances, as some countries use this symbol on detours for vehicles with dangerous goods.

values.title: End of no parking zone
values.desc: Different arrows may be used to show the right direction.

values.title: Proceed left
values.desc: Yellow for general roads with multiple lanes.

values.title: Proceed straight

values.title: Turn right

values.title: Drive straight or turn right

values.title: Pass on right
values.desc: Placed at the entrance to the tunnel. The length is also written on the sign.

values.title: Pass on left
values.desc: Shows destinations that may be reached through the same road at the next crossroads or exit.

values.title: Roundabout
values.desc: Steep hill ahead. Tire chains are required for trucks over 3,5 tonnes during severe winter conditions.

values.title: End of motor traffic road

values.title: Heavy traffic lane

values.title: End of heavy traffic lane
values.desc: Used when there are no symbols that represent the regulation or information. Depicted sign is common and says: “Does not apply to buses and taxis”.

values.title: Bus lane
values.desc: Arrows vary. Main sign applies after the turn.

values.title: Bus and taxi lane
values.desc: Symbol varies.

values.title: Car-pool lane
values.desc: Symbol varies. Priority road is represented by the thick line. Roads represented by thin lines have give way or stop signs for the priority road.

values.title: End of bus lane
values.desc: Indicates that parking is only allowed by given regulations when a valid parking ticket or disc is placed highly visible inside the windshield.

values.title: End of bus and taxi lane
values.desc: In this example, the times written only applies for cars.

values.title: End of car-pool lane
